cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper proposes novel mechanisms for domain-aware word embedding training, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI) concepts, which could place it in cs.IR and cs.AI, respectively. Finally, the paper proposes a joint learning paradigm, which could also relate to the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
